                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.6341 South American Development Co./52:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 2, 1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Department’s telegram No. 7, February 1, 7 p.m. Rivas, the South American
                    Development Company’s local agent, this morning <pb facs="0556" n="547"
                        xml:id="pg_547"/> interviewed General Enriquez who declared that he could
                    not grant a formal extension but would give an informal extension until February
                    5, noon, until which time he promised that no action will be taken by the
                    Government. I am therefore making no representations pending further
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
